cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL. 

This paper deals with Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (DCNNs) and their performance in computer vision tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the challenges of adding new information to a fixed dataset, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed adaptive hierarchical network structure also involves self-growth, which could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the organization of data into feature-driven super-classes, which could be related to cs.CL (Computation and Language).
